{"type":"articles","tags":["articles"],"uid":"the-big-glass","headline":"The big glass","standfirst":"","publishDate":"2011-03-10T13:47:12.000Z","promo":[{"key":"embeddedImage","value":{"non-repeat":{"caption":[{"type":"paragraph","content":{"text":"Since last week, Joanna Walsh has been creating a large-scale drawing, ‘Ars Moriendi’, on the glass wall in the Wellcome Collection lobby. We asked her what it was like to approach such a vast blank canvas and begin drawing, all in public. It’s always terrifying to approach a blank page, even more so when it [&hellip;]","spans":[]}}],"image":{"origin":{},"edit":{"background":"transparent","zoom":1,"crop":{"x":0,"y":0}},"thumbnails":{}}}}}],"credits":[],"series":[],"content":[{"key":"embeddedImage","value":{"non-repeat":{"caption":[{"type":"paragraph","content":{"text":"Ars Moriendi. All photos by Joanna Walsh.","spans":[]}}],"image":{"origin":{"url":"https://wellcomecollection.files.wordpress.com/2011/03/sp_a0418.jpg","width":450,"height":338},"width":450,"height":338,"url":"https://wellcomecollection.files.wordpress.com/2011/03/sp_a0418.jpg","edit":{"background":"transparent","zoom":1,"crop":{"x":0,"y":0}},"alt":"Ars Moriendi. All photos by Joanna Walsh.","thumbnails":{}},"weight":"default"}}},{"key":"paragraph","value":{"non-repeat":{"text":[{"type":"paragraph","content":{"text":"<em>Since last week, <strong>Joanna Walsh</strong> has been creating a large-scale drawing, ‘Ars Moriendi’, on the glass wall in the Wellcome Collection lobby. We asked her what it was like to approach such a vast blank canvas and begin drawing, all in public.</em>","spans":[]}}]}}},{"key":"paragraph","value":{"non-repeat":{"text":[{"type":"paragraph","content":{"text":"It’s always terrifying to approach a blank page, even more so when it measures around 5 x 12 metres.","spans":[]}}]}}},{"key":"paragraph","value":{"non-repeat":{"text":[{"type":"paragraph","content":{"text":"The panels of glass in the wall acted like a grid so I could more easily scale up my drawing.","spans":[]}}]}}},{"key":"paragraph","value":{"non-repeat":{"text":[{"type":"paragraph","content":{"text":"First I sketched out my design in chinagraph.","spans":[]}}]}}},{"key":"embeddedImage","value":{"non-repeat":{"caption":[{"type":"paragraph","content":{"text":"","spans":[]}}],"image":{"origin":{"url":"https://wellcomecollection.files.wordpress.com/2011/03/sp_a0401.jpg","width":450,"height":387},"width":450,"height":387,"url":"https://wellcomecollection.files.wordpress.com/2011/03/sp_a0401.jpg","edit":{"background":"transparent","zoom":1,"crop":{"x":0,"y":0}},"alt":"","thumbnails":{}},"weight":"default"}}},{"key":"paragraph","value":{"non-repeat":{"text":[{"type":"paragraph","content":{"text":"…before beginning to ink in the drawing.","spans":[]}}]}}},{"key":"paragraph","value":{"non-repeat":{"text":[{"type":"paragraph","content":{"text":"I’m using <a href=\"http://www.craftyarts.co.uk/acatalog/Uni_POSCA_Markers.html\">Posca paint pens</a> in white. They look striking against the background created by the black curtain drawn behind the glass. They’re semi-permanent. You can wipe over them gently without erasing the lines but if you scrub at them, or use window cleaner, they come off quite easily. I like the fact that this artwork is temporary. It frees me up to not worry so much about making mistakes which, paradoxically, means that I make fewer.","spans":[]}}]}}},{"key":"embeddedImage","value":{"non-repeat":{"caption":[{"type":"paragraph","content":{"text":"","spans":[]}}],"image":{"origin":{"url":"https://wellcomecollection.files.wordpress.com/2011/03/sp_a0403.jpg","width":450,"height":338},"width":450,"height":338,"url":"https://wellcomecollection.files.wordpress.com/2011/03/sp_a0403.jpg","edit":{"background":"transparent","zoom":1,"crop":{"x":0,"y":0}},"alt":"","thumbnails":{}},"weight":"default"}}},{"key":"paragraph","value":{"non-repeat":{"text":[{"type":"paragraph","content":{"text":"…but, as I’m used to being able to patch over any mistakes on my paper drawings in Photoshop,  one of my recurring thoughts is, “Where’s the CTRL+Z for live drawing?”","spans":[]}}]}}},{"key":"paragraph","value":{"non-repeat":{"text":[{"type":"paragraph","content":{"text":"After a few days the picture is definitely growing…","spans":[]}}]}}},{"key":"embeddedImage","value":{"non-repeat":{"caption":[{"type":"paragraph","content":{"text":"","spans":[]}}],"image":{"origin":{"url":"https://wellcomecollection.files.wordpress.com/2011/03/sp_a0408.jpg","width":450,"height":338},"width":450,"height":338,"url":"https://wellcomecollection.files.wordpress.com/2011/03/sp_a0408.jpg","edit":{"background":"transparent","zoom":1,"crop":{"x":0,"y":0}},"alt":"","thumbnails":{}},"weight":"default"}}},{"key":"paragraph","value":{"non-repeat":{"text":[{"type":"paragraph","content":{"text":"…which was one of the ideas I wanted to put into the drawing. At Sobell I noticed…","spans":[]}}]}}},{"key":"embeddedImage","value":{"non-repeat":{"caption":[{"type":"paragraph","content":{"text":"","spans":[]}}],"image":{"origin":{"url":"https://wellcomecollection.files.wordpress.com/2011/03/sp_a0413.jpg","width":450,"height":338},"width":450,"height":338,"url":"https://wellcomecollection.files.wordpress.com/2011/03/sp_a0413.jpg","edit":{"background":"transparent","zoom":1,"crop":{"x":0,"y":0}},"alt":"","thumbnails":{}},"weight":"default"}}},{"key":"paragraph","value":{"non-repeat":{"text":[{"type":"paragraph","content":{"text":"…how the outdoors continued indoors into floral curtains, flower arrangements, wood or laminate flooring and furniture just as…","spans":[]}}]}}},{"key":"embeddedImage","value":{"non-repeat":{"caption":[{"type":"paragraph","content":{"text":"","spans":[]}}],"image":{"origin":{"url":"https://wellcomecollection.files.wordpress.com/2011/03/sp_a0411.jpg","width":450,"height":338},"width":450,"height":338,"url":"https://wellcomecollection.files.wordpress.com/2011/03/sp_a0411.jpg","edit":{"background":"transparent","zoom":1,"crop":{"x":0,"y":0}},"alt":"","thumbnails":{}},"weight":"default"}}},{"key":"paragraph","value":{"non-repeat":{"text":[{"type":"paragraph","content":{"text":"…the inside of the bodies of patients are somehow extended into tubes and machines, and our…","spans":[]}}]}}},{"key":"embeddedImage","value":{"non-repeat":{"caption":[{"type":"paragraph","content":{"text":"","spans":[]}}],"image":{"origin":{"url":"https://wellcomecollection.files.wordpress.com/2011/03/sp_a0417.jpg","width":450,"height":338},"width":450,"height":338,"url":"https://wellcomecollection.files.wordpress.com/2011/03/sp_a0417.jpg","edit":{"background":"transparent","zoom":1,"crop":{"x":0,"y":0}},"alt":"","thumbnails":{}},"weight":"default"}}},{"key":"paragraph","value":{"non-repeat":{"text":[{"type":"paragraph","content":{"text":"…concept of what is ‘right’ and ‘natural’ in a body, in a way of living and dying, trembles.","spans":[]}}]}}},{"key":"embeddedImage","value":{"non-repeat":{"caption":[{"type":"paragraph","content":{"text":"","spans":[]}}],"image":{"origin":{"url":"https://wellcomecollection.files.wordpress.com/2011/03/sp_a0421.jpg","width":450,"height":436},"width":450,"height":436,"url":"https://wellcomecollection.files.wordpress.com/2011/03/sp_a0421.jpg","edit":{"background":"transparent","zoom":1,"crop":{"x":0,"y":0}},"alt":"","thumbnails":{}},"weight":"default"}}},{"key":"paragraph","value":{"non-repeat":{"text":[{"type":"paragraph","content":{"text":"I spent the final days putting in…","spans":[]}}]}}},{"key":"embeddedImage","value":{"non-repeat":{"caption":[{"type":"paragraph","content":{"text":"","spans":[]}}],"image":{"origin":{"url":"https://wellcomecollection.files.wordpress.com/2011/03/sp_a0420.jpg","width":450,"height":431},"width":450,"height":431,"url":"https://wellcomecollection.files.wordpress.com/2011/03/sp_a0420.jpg","edit":{"background":"transparent","zoom":1,"crop":{"x":0,"y":0}},"alt":"","thumbnails":{}},"weight":"default"}}},{"key":"paragraph","value":{"non-repeat":{"text":[{"type":"paragraph","content":{"text":"textures…","spans":[]}}]}}},{"key":"embeddedImage","value":{"non-repeat":{"caption":[{"type":"paragraph","content":{"text":"","spans":[]}}],"image":{"origin":{"url":"https://wellcomecollection.files.wordpress.com/2011/03/sp_a0419.jpg","width":960,"height":672},"width":960,"height":672,"url":"https://wellcomecollection.files.wordpress.com/2011/03/sp_a0419.jpg","edit":{"background":"transparent","zoom":1,"crop":{"x":0,"y":0}},"alt":"","thumbnails":{}},"weight":"default"}}},{"key":"paragraph","value":{"non-repeat":{"text":[{"type":"paragraph","content":{"text":"‘mark-making’…","spans":[]}}]}}},{"key":"embeddedImage","value":{"non-repeat":{"caption":[{"type":"paragraph","content":{"text":"","spans":[]}}],"image":{"origin":{"url":"https://wellcomecollection.files.wordpress.com/2011/03/sp_a0415.jpg","width":450,"height":360},"width":450,"height":360,"url":"https://wellcomecollection.files.wordpress.com/2011/03/sp_a0415.jpg","edit":{"background":"transparent","zoom":1,"crop":{"x":0,"y":0}},"alt":"","thumbnails":{}},"weight":"default"}}},{"key":"paragraph","value":{"non-repeat":{"text":[{"type":"paragraph","content":{"text":"As I’ve been working <em>in situ</em> at the Wellcome Collection, people feel free to come up and talk to me.","spans":[]}}]}}},{"key":"paragraph","value":{"non-repeat":{"text":[{"type":"paragraph","content":{"text":"So far I’ve heard…","spans":[]}}]}}},{"key":"embeddedImage","value":{"non-repeat":{"caption":[{"type":"paragraph","content":{"text":"","spans":[]}}],"image":{"origin":{"url":"https://wellcomecollection.files.wordpress.com/2011/03/sp_a0407.jpg","width":960,"height":1076},"width":960,"height":1076,"url":"https://wellcomecollection.files.wordpress.com/2011/03/sp_a0407.jpg","edit":{"background":"transparent","zoom":1,"crop":{"x":0,"y":0}},"alt":"","thumbnails":{}},"weight":"default"}}},{"key":"paragraph","value":{"non-repeat":{"text":[{"type":"paragraph","content":{"text":"lots of questions about what kinds of pens I’m using…","spans":[]}}]}}},{"key":"embeddedImage","value":{"non-repeat":{"caption":[{"type":"paragraph","content":{"text":"","spans":[]}}],"image":{"origin":{"url":"https://wellcomecollection.files.wordpress.com/2011/03/sp_a0410.jpg","width":960,"height":788},"width":960,"height":788,"url":"https://wellcomecollection.files.wordpress.com/2011/03/sp_a0410.jpg","edit":{"background":"transparent","zoom":1,"crop":{"x":0,"y":0}},"alt":"","thumbnails":{}},"weight":"default"}}},{"key":"paragraph","value":{"non-repeat":{"text":[{"type":"paragraph","content":{"text":"many confessions about deaths experienced: someone who needed to express her anger about the gaps in her sister-in-law’s care…","spans":[]}}]}}},{"key":"embeddedImage","value":{"non-repeat":{"caption":[{"type":"paragraph","content":{"text":"","spans":[]}}],"image":{"origin":{"url":"https://wellcomecollection.files.wordpress.com/2011/03/sp_a0412.jpg","width":450,"height":338},"width":450,"height":338,"url":"https://wellcomecollection.files.wordpress.com/2011/03/sp_a0412.jpg","edit":{"background":"transparent","zoom":1,"crop":{"x":0,"y":0}},"alt":"","thumbnails":{}},"weight":"default"}}},{"key":"paragraph","value":{"non-repeat":{"text":[{"type":"paragraph","content":{"text":"theories: a (stunningly beautiful) young Egyptian Moslem who thinks about plans for her own death frequently as she has witnessed ‘so many bad deaths’ and a middle-aged man who is angry with Dylan Thomas’s angry wish to ‘not go gentle into that good night’ and would like more cultural acceptance of ‘ebbing away’…","spans":[]}}]}}},{"key":"embeddedImage","value":{"non-repeat":{"caption":[{"type":"paragraph","content":{"text":"","spans":[]}}],"image":{"origin":{"url":"https://wellcomecollection.files.wordpress.com/2011/03/sp_a0414.jpg","width":450,"height":338},"width":450,"height":338,"url":"https://wellcomecollection.files.wordpress.com/2011/03/sp_a0414.jpg","edit":{"background":"transparent","zoom":1,"crop":{"x":0,"y":0}},"alt":"","thumbnails":{}},"weight":"default"}}},{"key":"paragraph","value":{"non-repeat":{"text":[{"type":"paragraph","content":{"text":"and reactions from medics – who are usually very positive about what I’m doing, saying that it reflects their own experiences in palliative care. This means a lot to me.","spans":[]}}]}}},{"key":"paragraph","value":{"non-repeat":{"text":[{"type":"paragraph","content":{"text":"Oh, and…","spans":[]}}]}}},{"key":"paragraph","value":{"non-repeat":{"text":[{"type":"paragraph","content":{"text":"One question about whether I get enough work and whether I can make a living from what I do. This was so unexpected I somehow felt obliged to answer it.","spans":[]}}]}}},{"key":"paragraph","value":{"non-repeat":{"text":[{"type":"paragraph","content":{"text":"<em>Joanna will be drawing again at Wellcome Collection this Friday (11 March).</em>","spans":[]}}]}}}]}